{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place bread into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place parsley and onion into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add livers, eggs, salt, pepper and reserved breadcrumbs and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside for 10 minutes to thicken.","Place a large frying pan over medium-high heat and add oil. Working in batches, place 6 x ¼ cupfuls of mixture into frying pan and fry for approx. 3 minutes each side, until slightly pink inside or cooked to your liking (makes 12 fritters in total). Transfer to a plate, then serve as desired (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["150 g day old bread (approx. 4 slices), crusts removed (and torn into pieces - see Tips)","3 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","150 g brown onion, cut into halves","500 g chicken livers, trimmed","2 eggs","½ tsp salt","½ tsp ground black pepper","oil (approx. 2 tablespoons), for frying"]}],"id":"r293370","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-G9WWBcdrfZs\/XZQHfRDXR5I\/AAAAAAAAcIw\/gpR6CnQIIPE4Trj1uEWMvQ3NQ6DLVz2TgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_kHHWPFZQmt94tFx-.png","title":"Country-style chicken liver fritters","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.5 g","fat":"6.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"6.7 g","calories":"511.8 kJ \/ 121.9 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, large frying pan (26 cm), plate, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["You can replace bread with a gluten free bread to make breadcrumbs. Choose a bread with a light texture. A dense bread will not work for this recipe.","We served our fritters with <i>Rye loaf<\/i> and <i>Quick beetroot relish<\/i> (please refer to the recipes on this recipe chip) and pickles as part of a ploughman's platter. But you can also serve them with mashed potatoes or as burger patties (burgers are a great way to introduce children to liver and boost their iron intake!)."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","35m","12 portions"]}